OL,3,C'World's oldest calendar' found carved
OL,4,Conto ancient monument
OL,6,FThe findings, published in the journal
OL,7,FTime And Mind, suggest these ancient
OL,8,Fhumans used precession, the wobble in
OL,9,FEarth's axis which affects the
OL,10,Fmovement of constellations across the
OL,11,Fsky, to record dates.
OL,13,FAdditionally, the carvings appear to
OL,14,Fdepict a comet strike that wiped out
OL,15,Flarge animals 13,000 years ago and
OL,16,Ftriggered a mini ice age that lasted
OL,17,F1,200 years.
