OL,3,C'World's oldest calendar' found carved
OL,4,Conto ancient monument
OL,6,FThe team also uncovered a second
OL,7,Fpillar showing a meteor stream that
OL,8,Flasted 27 days.
OL,10,FThe Gobekli Tepe site, which features
OL,11,Fthe oldest-known man-made structures,
OL,12,Fwas built by hunter-gatherers between
OL,13,F9,600 and 8,200 BC, predating
OL,14,FStonehenge by more than 6,000 years.
OL,16,FThe monument's exact purpose has
OL,17,Fpuzzled experts for decades, although
OL,18,Fmany believe the place was used in
OL,19,Fconnection with rituals, such as
OL,20,Ffunerals.
